page.title: 01N.W. of Dunerdale Valley
page.content: Part of the english lake District national park and includes National Trust and Forrestry Commission Land. A primarily elevated area dominated by Harter Fell Mountain with its panoramic views rocy outcrops heather rough pasture and particularly on the lower easter flank a plantation of conifers mixed with some deciduous trees. A fair amount of wetland exists to the west of harter Fell. The river duddon runs north to south of Harter fell which is not its source of flow. The river has waterfall and gorge. A public car park is situated from which marked trails and walks are used by visitor and tourist. Sheep predominate with only a handful of cattle.
